# Ëünic'han – English Dictionary

## 1. Alphabet & Phonetics Reference

| Upper | Lower | IPA | English Example |
|-------|-------|-----|----------------|
| A | a | /a/ | father |
| Ā | ā | /eɪ/ | play |
| Æ̃ | æ̃ | /eɪ/ | rain, pain (distinct from Ā) |
| B | b | /b/ | blood |
| C | c | /k/ | clock |
| C̈ | c̈ | /s/ | sedate |
| Ć | ć | /ʃ/ | she |
| Ch | ch | /tʃ/ | church, cache, lunch |
| D | d | /d/ | door |
| E | e | /ɛ/ | egg |
| Ë | ë | /eɪ/ | Jane, ray, cane |
| È | è | /a/ or /ər/ | rang, tank / transfer, letter |
| É | é | /aɪ/ | die, try, cry |
| Ē | ē | /i/ | bit, dean, seen |
| Ēã | ēã | /joʊ/ | yoga, trio |
| F | f | /f/ | fate |
| G | g | / ḥāʼ / | Ahmed (voiced h) |
| G̀ | g̀ | /g/ | grass |
| Ǵ | ǵ | /ʒ/ | measure, garage, entourage |
| H | h | /h/ | house |
| I | i | /ɪ/ | pin |
| Ḯ | ḯ | /aɪ/ | right |
| J | j | /dʒ/ | jail |
| K | k | /k/ | kitchen |
| L | l | /l/ | line |
| M | m | /m/ | mobile |
| N | n | /n/ | new |
| O | o | /ɒ/ | top |
| Ò | ò | /oʊ/ | go |
| Oo | oo | /uː/ | pool, boot |
| P | p | /p/ | plant |
| R | r | /r/ | random |
| S | s | /s/ | sleep |
| Ś | ś | /ʃ/ | shark |
| S̀ | s̀ | /z/ | zero |
| Se | se | /z/ | rose |
| T | t | /t/ | train |
| Th | th | /θ/ or /ð/ | thin / then |
| U | u | /ʊ/ (or /w/ after G, silent after Ēã) | pun, mum |
| Ü | ü | /uː/ | pool, boot |
| Ú | ú | /ʊ/ | put, foot (short oo) |
| V | v | /v/ | vital |
| W | w | /w/ | water |
| X | x | /z/ | zoo |
| Ẍ | ẍ | /dʒ/ | judge |
| X̀ | x̀ | /h/ | hello |
| X́ | x́ | /ɛks/ | exit |
| X́̀ | x́̀ | — | silent (both accents) |
| Y | y | /j/ | yes |
| Ÿ | ÿ | /ɪ/ or /aɪ/ | bit / my |
| Z | z | /z/ | zebra |

**Apostrophe ('):** A very quick pause. Prevents two letters from blending into a new sound.  
Example: c'h = /k-h/ (not /tʃ/).

