Should I open it in external editor?

Short answer: no—you don’t need to.
Stick with the built-in editor in Keyman Developer for now.

🔹 Why the built-in editor is better (at this stage)
✅ Syntax highlighting for .kmn (helps spot mistakes)

✅ Error messages show up immediately when you compile

✅ One-click compile + test

✅ Less chance of breaking formatting

If you open it externally (like in Notepad or VS Code), you lose those advantages unless you’re already very comfortable with Keyman syntax.

🔹 When an external editor does make sense
Only consider it if:

Your file gets very large

You want advanced search/replace

You’re confident with .kmn syntax already

Even then, most people still come back to Keyman Developer to compile and debug.

🔹 Best workflow right now
Open eunichan_keyboard.kmn inside Keyman Developer

Paste your rules

Click Compile

Fix any errors immediately

🔹 One small tip (this will save you stress)
Make small changes like:

Add 2–3 rules

Compile

Test

Don’t paste everything at once—you’ll avoid “where did I mess up?” headaches.

