iphone 5 (landscape) is what I'm seeing and can only change to iphone 5 (portrait)

Yep—that’s normal 👍
What you’re seeing is just the preview device, not your actual keyboard limit.

In Keyman Developer, the touch layout editor uses iPhone 5 as a generic preview frame. It doesn’t mean your keyboard will only work on iPhones.

🔹 What it actually means
iPhone 5 (portrait / landscape) = just a design preview

Your keyboard will still work on:

Android phones

Different screen sizes

Keyman automatically scales your layout

🔹 Why you can’t change it
Keyman:

Uses a fixed reference device

Doesn’t let you switch to Android previews (annoying, but harmless)

🔹 What you should focus on instead
Design for:

✅ Portrait mode first (most important)

✅ Comfortable key spacing

✅ Long-press menus

Landscape is optional unless you really care about it.

🔹 Practical design advice for your keyboard
For Ëünic'han:

Vowel keys (very important)
Make sure these are easy to reach:

e → long press:

ë, ē, é, è, æ̃, ēã

o → ò, oo

u → ü, ú

Consonants with variants
c → ć, c̈

g → g̀, ǵ

s → ś, s̀

x → ẍ, x́, x̀, x́̀

Special key
Keep ' very accessible (your language depends on it)

🔹 Important mindset shift
Don’t try to match a specific phone.

Instead:

Build a flexible layout → Keyman adapts it to all screens

