Can I change the numbers to custom doodles/symbols I made for numbers?

Yes—you can, but there’s an important limitation you should know first:

👉 You can replace number keys with your own symbols on your custom keyboard,
❗ but apps won’t treat them as real numbers unless you map them carefully.

🔹 What you can do in Keyman Developer
✅ Option 1: Replace visible number keys
In your .keyman-touch-layout:

Edit the number row (or symbol layer)

Replace:

1 2 3 4 5 6 7 8 9 0

With your doodles:

𐓐 𐓑 𐓒 … (example style)

So visually:

[𐓐] [𐓑] [𐓒] ...
✅ Option 2: Keep numbers underneath (SMART way)
This is what I strongly recommend:

Key shows: your symbol

Output: real number

Example:

Key shows	Output
𐓐	1
𐓑	2
𐓒	3
This way:

Apps still understand numbers ✅

Your language still looks unique ✅

🔹 How to do that
In .keyman-touch-layout:

Set:

text → your symbol (what you see)

output → number (what gets typed)

🔹 Option 3: Fully custom number system
If you want:

Your symbols to be the actual typed characters

Then:

Map keys to your Unicode characters in .kmn

Example:

+ '1' > '𐓐'
+ '2' > '𐓑'
🔹 ⚠️ Important tradeoffs
If you go full custom:

❌ Problems:
Calculators won’t recognize them

Forms may reject input

Searching numbers won’t work

Copy/paste into other apps may break

🔹 Best Hybrid Design (recommended)
Do this:

Tap → outputs real number (1)

Long press → outputs your symbol (𐓐)

That gives you:

Practical use ✅

Language identity ✅

🔹 Bonus idea (very clean)
Use your system like this:

Normal typing → real numbers

Writing in Ëünic'han → long-press symbols

