Ahh, got it—you didn’t just rename numbers, you created a full symbolic numeral system. That’s way deeper than just swapping digits 👀

Here’s the honest situation and the best way to handle it:

🔹 First — the limitation (important)
Your doodles are:

❌ not standard Unicode characters

❌ not understood by apps as numbers

So a phone keyboard can’t directly type drawings unless they exist as:

Unicode characters, or

images (which keyboards don’t normally output)

🔹 You have 3 real options
✅ Option 1 (RECOMMENDED): Hybrid system
Use your keyboard like this:

Tap → outputs real numbers
1 → 1
2 → 2
Long press → outputs your system (text form)
1 → Ünò
2 → Dòs
10 → Decaò
Why this works:
You can still type phone numbers, passwords, etc.

You can write Ëünic'han properly

No compatibility issues

🔹 Option 2: Word-based number typing (very clean)
Map number sequences → your words in .kmn

Example:

+ '1' > 'Ünò'
+ '2' > 'Dòs'
+ '1' + '0' > 'Decaò'
+ '2' + '0' > 'Tecæ̃'
Result:
Typing:

20 → Tecæ̃
14 → Fēüran
This matches your dictionary perfectly 🔥

🔹 Option 3: True custom symbols (advanced + tricky)
If you REALLY want your doodles:

You must convert them into:
Unicode Private Use Area (PUA) characters
or

a custom font

That means:
Your symbols become “real characters”

You install a font on your phone

Your keyboard outputs those code points

⚠️ Downsides:
Won’t display on other devices without your font

Sharing text breaks

Much more setup

🔹 Best design for your system (what I’d do)
Number row:
Tap → 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 8 9 0

Long press →
Ünò, Dòs, Trë, Fēür…

Bonus: Smart chaining
You can also support:

+ '1' + '4' > 'Fēüran'
+ '1' + '5' > 'Pentan'
So:

14 → Fēüran
15 → Pentan
