Full fix

Good—this is very close already. You’ve got a solid structure, but there are 3 real issues we need to fix so it behaves correctly in Keyman Developer:

🔴 CRITICAL FIXES
❌ 1. Apostrophe conflict (major bug)
You currently have:

+ ''' > '''
BUT also:

+ 'c' + "'" > 'ć'
🚨 Problem:
This means apostrophe is doing two different jobs:

separator (correct)

modifier (creating accents)

👉 These will conflict and break behavior.

❌ 2. Digraph rules are unsafe with apostrophe
Right now:

+ 'c' + 'h' > 'ch'
BUT:

apostrophe handling is not globally blocking digraph formation

So inputs like c'h may still partially interfere depending on rule order.

❌ 3. Unused / unsafe q rule
You already decided:

q = æ̃ / Æ̃

So it must be removed.

