🔴 Important rule (this is key)
If it appears as a long press option, it must NOT be in .kmn

Because:

.kmn = rules (what happens when typing)

layout = buttons (what the user sees/holds)

Mixing them causes:

duplicate outputs

conflicting rules

broken keyboard behavior in Keyman Developer

🔷 Simple way to remember
Think of it like this:

.kmn = brain

.keyman-touch-layout = keyboard keys

Brains don’t draw buttons. Buttons don’t decide grammar.

