unichan_keyboard.kmn - info: "C:\Program Files (x86)\Keyman\Keyman Developer\kmc.cmd" "build" "--log-format" "tsv" "--log-level" "info" "D:\Av-Atarians\Keyboard\eunichan_keyboard\source\eunichan_keyboard.kmn" "--out-file" "D:\Av-Atarians\Keyboard\eunichan_keyboard\build\eunichan_keyboard.kmx" "--compiler-warnings-as-errors"
eunichan_keyboard.kmn - info KM05002: Building eunichan_keyboard.kmn
eunichan_keyboard.kmn:4 - error KM0200A: Invalid token found
eunichan_keyboard.kmn - info KM05007: eunichan_keyboard.kmn failed to build.

That error is a classic Keyman compiler complaint—and it’s usually something small but strict.

🔴 The actual problem
The line causing this:

store(&NAME) 'Ëünic'han Keyboard'
👉 The apostrophe inside Ëünic'han is breaking the string.

Keyman reads:

'Ëünic' → string ends here ❌

then sees han → invalid token ❌

That’s exactly what KM0200A: Invalid token found means.

🟢 The fix (very simple)
You must escape the apostrophe inside the string.

✔ Correct version:
store(&NAME) 'Ëünic''han Keyboard'
👉 Notice:

'' (two apostrophes) = one literal '

🔧 Apply this fix anywhere needed
Check ALL lines like this:

❌ Wrong:
'Ëünic'han'
✔ Correct:
'Ëünic''han'
🔍 Why this matters
Keyman uses:

'...' for strings

so any ' inside must be doubled

Same rule as SQL strings, if you’ve seen that.

🟢 After fixing
Save file

Click Compile Keyboard again

You should now see:

KM05007: Build successful
⚠️ If you still get errors
Send:

