🔴 What the error means
KM0200D: Invalid 'version' statement
KM02081: The keyboard file is an old version
👉 This is caused by this line in your file:

store(&VERSION) '2.0'
Problem:
In modern Keyman Developer,
&VERSION is deprecated / invalid for .kmn keyboards.

🟢 The fix (do this exactly)
❌ REMOVE this line completely:
store(&VERSION) '2.0'
✔ KEEP this instead:
store(&KEYBOARDVERSION) '2.0'
That’s the correct modern version tag.

🔧 Your header should now look like this:
store(&NAME) 'Ëünic''han Keyboard'
store(&KEYBOARDVERSION) '2.0'
store(&TARGETS) 'androidphone'
store(&COPYRIGHT) 'Copyright © Dickson Chiemezue Oko-Ọkpara'
🔍 Why this happens
Keyman used to support:

&VERSION (old format)

Now it uses:

&KEYBOARDVERSION (new standard)

So the compiler rejects the old one.

