Alright—that message means the compiler crashed internally, not just a syntax error. That usually happens when the file has something it can’t safely parse (often invisible or encoding-related).

Let’s fix this the reliable way instead of chasing ghosts.

🔴 What’s likely causing it
From your file, the risky parts are:

Ë, Æ̃, ǵ, etc. → Unicode characters

Possible UTF-16 or mixed encoding (you already hit this earlier)

Copy/paste introducing hidden characters

👉 When Keyman hits bad encoding, it sometimes crashes instead of giving a clean error.

🟢 Fix it properly (this works 99% of the time)
✅ Step 1 — Set encoding correctly
In VS Code:

Bottom-right corner → click encoding (probably says UTF-16 or something)

Click → Save with Encoding

Choose:

UTF-8
👉 Not UTF-8 with BOM, just plain UTF-8

✅ Step 2 — Recreate the file cleanly
Do NOT keep editing the old file.

Create a new file:

eunichan_keyboard_clean.kmn
