UTF-8 with BOM is what it already id

Good catch—that detail matters.

👉 UTF-8 with BOM is usually fine in Keyman Developer, but in practice it can trigger weird compiler behavior (including the crash you just saw), especially with combining characters like æ̃.

🔴 What I want you to change
Even though it looks correct, switch it to:

UTF-8 (no BOM)
🟢 How to do it (VS Code)
Bottom right → click UTF-8 with BOM

Click Save with Encoding

Select:

UTF-8
🔴 Why this matters (important)
Your keyboard uses:

æ̃ → this is actually:

æ (U+00E6)

̃ (combining tilde U+0303)

When combined with:

BOM marker

or copied Unicode text

👉 Keyman sometimes misreads the stream → internal crash instead of normal error

🟢 Also fix THIS (very important)
Change these lines:

❌ Current:
+ 'q' > 'æ̃'
+ 'Q' > 'Æ̃'
✔ Safer version:
+ 'q' > U+00E6 U+0303
+ 'Q' > U+00C6 U+0303
👉 This avoids all encoding ambiguity.

