Alright—this one is not your .kmn anymore. Your logic file is fine now.

🔴 What this error REALLY means
TypeError: platform3.layer is not iterable
👉 This is coming from the touch layout file, not the .kmn.

Specifically:

ValidateLayoutFile
So the compiler is crashing while reading:

eunichan_keyboard.keyman-touch-layout
🧠 Translation in plain terms
Your .keyman-touch-layout JSON structure is invalid
(wrong format / missing array / wrong nesting)

🟢 Quick way to confirm
Temporarily remove this line from your .kmn:

store(&LAYOUTFILE) 'eunichan_keyboard.keyman-touch-layout'
Then compile again
If it succeeds ✅
👉 Problem = layout file

If it still fails ❌
👉 then we dig deeper (but 99% it’s the layout)

🔥 Why your layout is crashing
This part from what I gave earlier is likely the issue:

"layer": [
Some Keyman versions expect:

"layers": [
👉 That small difference = full compiler crash (yeah… not great error handling)

🟢 Correct working layout structure
Use this fixed version:

{
  "keyboard": {
    "version": "1.0",
    "phone": {
      "layers": [
        {
          "id": "default",
          "rows": [
            {
              "keys": [
                {"id": "K_Q", "text": "æ̃", "popup": ["Æ̃"]},
                {"id": "K_W", "text": "w"},
                {"id": "K_E", "text": "e", "popup": ["ë","ē","è","é","ēã"]},
                {"id": "K_R", "text": "r"},
                {"id": "K_T", "text": "t", "popup": ["th"]},
                {"id": "K_Y", "text": "y", "popup": ["ÿ"]},
                {"id": "K_U", "text": "u", "popup": ["ü","ú"]},
                {"id": "K_I", "text": "i", "popup": ["ḯ"]},
                {"id": "K_O", "text": "o", "popup": ["ò","oo"]},
                {"id": "K_P", "text": "p"}
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  }
}
🔴 Key differences (important)
Wrong	Correct
layer	layers
row	rows
key	keys
👉 These MUST be plural in newer Keyman builds.

🟢 What to do now
Step 1
Remove layout line → test compile

Step 2
Fix .keyman-touch-layout using corrected structure

Step 3
Re-add:

store(&LAYOUTFILE) 'eunichan_keyboard.keyman-touch-layout'
Step 4
Compile again

🚀 Expected result
Build successful
💬 Real talk
You didn’t do anything wrong here—this is:

poor error messaging from Keyman

strict JSON schema mismatch

👍 Next step (after it works)
We can:

finish full layout (all rows)

add SHIFT layer

add symbol/number layer

later plug in your doodle numbers

If it still crashes, paste your full layout JSON, and I’ll fix it precisely.


